t.wiszniewski@gmail.com.message:
Allow reserved words as keys in ES6 module context

`<script type="module">` and *node*/*iojs* code imply full support of ES5.

Code transpiled by *babel* is also perfecly safe:

```js
$ cat <<––– | babel
const superman = {
  default: { clark: 'kent' },
  private: true
};
–––
"use strict";

var superman = {
   "default": { clark: "kent" },
   "private": true
};
```

